title: Sidewall, ca. 1790
provenance: Found at Barclay's Bank, 7 Manor Street, Bridlington, the former residence of Sir Henry Boynton, who in 1825 converted two houses, built about 1790, into one. This paper was applied before the remodelling.
description: Incomplete repeat of a twisting floral and leaf design, green, yellow, and black, on a brown patterned ground.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, ca. 1790.
ca. 1790. Block-printed, handmade paper. Gift of E.A. Entwisle. 1953-188-2.
